attributes.name: Payment Type
attributes.definition: The type of payment made.

attributes.name: Payment
attributes.definition: The amount of the payment made.

attributes.name: Payment Date
attributes.definition: The date of the payment.

attributes.name: Account Payor
attributes.definition: The account that made the payment.

attributes.name: Cash Entered Date
attributes.definition: The date that the payment cash was entered into the system.

attributes.name: Payment Category 1
attributes.definition: The category of payment, either Cash Disbursement, Commission or Premium.

attributes.name: Payment Category 2
attributes.definition: The second payment category.

attributes.name: Payment Category 3
attributes.definition: The third Payment Category.

attributes.name: Cash Entry Number
attributes.definition: The entry number associated with a cash deposit.

attributes.name: Check Number
attributes.definition: The number of the payment check received.

attributes.name: Entry Method
attributes.definition: The way that a payment was entered, either Manual, E-Check or Web Credit Card.

attributes.name: NSF Date
attributes.definition: The date that an insufficient funds notice is received from the bank on a payment.

attributes.name: NSF Flag
attributes.definition: An indicator on the payment if the payment was rejected by the bank for insufficient funds.

attributes.name: Entry Type
attributes.definition: The type of payment entry, either Internal or External.

attributes.name: Downpayment Flag
attributes.definition: An indicator the marks a payment as being a downpayment and not a payment against an invoice.

attributes.name: First Refund Date
attributes.definition: The date of the first refund issued against a payment.

attributes.name: Receipt Amount
attributes.definition: The net amount of a payment subtracting out any amount that was refunded.

attributes.name: Refund Amount
attributes.definition: The total amount refunded against a specific payment.

attributes.name: Reissued Check Flag
attributes.definition: An indicator marking a transaction as being associated with a Reissued Check.

attributes.name: Payment Transaction Type
attributes.definition: The type of the payment transaction, either Issued or Voided.

attributes.name: Payment Sub Type
attributes.definition: The granular type of payment, with a heirarchical relationship with Payment Type and values of ACH install, ACH downpay, Credit Card install, Credit Card Downpay.

attributes.name: Payment Process Type
attributes.definition: The type of processing on the payment. Enumaration is Honored, NSF, Outstanding.

entities.name: Invoice Payment Assignment
entities.definition: Portions or all of invoice payments assignment amounts associated with specific Invoice Lines.

attributes.name: Payment
attributes.definition: The payment associated with the assignment.

attributes.name: Invoice Line
attributes.definition: The invoice line associated with the payment assignment record.

attributes.name: Assignment Amount
attributes.definition: The amount from a payment assigned to a specific invoice line.

attributes.name: Assignment Date
attributes.definition: The date that the payment assignment was made.

attributes.name: Assignment Type
attributes.definition: The type of assignment done, either automatic or payor requested.

attributes.name: Writeoff Flag
attributes.definition: An flag on an assignment record reflecting that the associated invoice line has been written off with a Yes or No value.

entities.name: Billing Account
entities.definition: The account that an invoice is billed to.

attributes.name: Account Number
attributes.definition: The System Account number for the Account.

attributes.name: Account Suspended Flag
attributes.definition: Flag indicating if an account has been suspended.

attributes.name: Account Suspension Reason
attributes.definition: The reason that an Account has been suspended.

attributes.name: Account Name
attributes.definition: The name of the account.

entities.name: Invoice
entities.definition: The invoice provided to the billing account for payment.

attributes.name: Billing Account
attributes.definition: The account that is responsible for paying the Invoice.

attributes.name: Invoice Due Date
attributes.definition: The Date by which the Invoice must be paid.

attributes.name: Invoice Number
attributes.definition: The Invoice Number as assigned from the Billing Source System.

attributes.name: Invoice Generation Status
attributes.definition: The Invoice Generation Status as it exists in the source system.

attributes.name: Invoice Date
attributes.definition: The date that the Invoice is generated.

attributes.name: Invoice
attributes.definition: The invoice associated with the invoice line.

attributes.name: Amount Due
attributes.definition: The amount due for the invoice line.

attributes.name: Billing Line
attributes.definition: The Billing Line record associated with the Invoice line.

attributes.name: Payable Flag
attributes.definition: This flag indicates if an Invoice Line is payable or not.

attributes.name: Billing Account
attributes.definition: The Account being billed.

attributes.name: Bill Plan
attributes.definition: The plan associated with the billing schedule.

attributes.name: Bill Plan Code
attributes.definition: The code for the bill plan associated with the billing schedule.

attributes.name: Bill Date
attributes.definition: The date that an Invoice is scheduled to be generated.

attributes.name: EFT Date
attributes.definition: The date that an EFT transaction is scheduled to withdraw from the bank.

attributes.name: Bill Mode
attributes.definition: The type of Billing associated with the schedule, either Agent Bill or Direct Bill.

attributes.name: Installment Premium Flag
attributes.definition: A yes/no flag indicating if a specific bill schedule record is installment.

attributes.name: Bill Payment Type
attributes.definition: This is the type of billing for the scheduled bill, either EFT or Non-EFT.

attributes.name: Bill Frequency
attributes.definition: The frequency of billing within the Bill Schedule.

attributes.name: Billing Account Type
attributes.definition: This is the type of Account being billed, either Agency or Direct.

attributes.name: Billing Schedule
attributes.definition: The billing schedule that the billing line is associated with.

attributes.name: Billing Amount
attributes.definition: The overall amount associated with the billing line.

attributes.name: Written Premium
attributes.definition: The written premium record that the billing line is associated with.

attributes.name: Billing Premium
attributes.definition: The amount of premium in the billing line.

attributes.name: Claim
attributes.definition: The claim associated with the Claim Transaction.

attributes.name: Transaction Date
attributes.definition: The Date of the Claim Transaction.

attributes.name: Transaction Type
attributes.definition: The type of Claim Transaction

attributes.name: Settle Date
attributes.definition: The date that the claim transaction settles against the bank.

attributes.name: Reversal Flag
attributes.definition: An indicator on the record marking transactions that were reversed.

attributes.name: Claim Transaction Id
attributes.definition: The system identifier for a claim transaction.

attributes.name: Transaction Payee
attributes.definition: The payee on the claim transaction.

attributes.name: Sent Date
attributes.definition: The date that a claim payment was sent.

attributes.name: Check Type
attributes.definition: The type of check, either Escheat or something else.

attributes.name: Check Number
attributes.definition: This is the check number associated with a Claim Transaction.

attributes.name: Reserve Amount
attributes.definition: This is the reserve amount associated with a Claim Transaction.

attributes.name: Payment Amount
attributes.definition: This is the payment amount associated with a Claim Transaction.

entities.name: Written Premium
entities.definition: The amount of premium that an account pays for coverage within a specified term.

attributes.name: Term
attributes.definition: The policy term associated with the written premium.

attributes.name: Transaction Date
attributes.definition: The date of the written premium transaction.

attributes.name: Agency
attributes.definition: The agency that sold the written premium.

attributes.name: Full Term Written Premium
attributes.definition: The dollars of premium if the premium had been in effect for the full term.

attributes.name: Written Premium Amount
attributes.definition: The amount of written premium.

attributes.name: Annualized Written Premium
attributes.definition: The written premium amount annualized, or prorated to the amount that would be paid for a 365 day term.

attributes.name: Transaction Reason
attributes.definition: The reason for a transaction, either an issue, an endorsement, a cancellation or a reinstatement.

attributes.name: Cancel Type
attributes.definition: The type of a cancellation, either Flat or Prorated.

attributes.name: Cancel Reason
attributes.definition: The reason for a cancellation, either non-payment, client choice, etc.

attributes.name: Agency Name
attributes.definition: The name of the Agency.

attributes.name: Agency Number
attributes.definition: The system number for the Agency.

attributes.name: Market Segment
attributes.definition: The Market Segment of the Term.

attributes.name: Underwriting Date
attributes.definition: The Date that the policy was underwritten.

attributes.name: Term Effective Date
attributes.definition: The date that the term becomes effective.

attributes.name: Term Effective End Date
attributes.definition: The Term Effective End Date.

attributes.name: Pending Cancel Date
attributes.definition: The future date that a policy is set to cancel.

attributes.name: Rescind Flag
attributes.definition: An indicator on the policy term if a policy has been rescinded.

attributes.name: Business Type
attributes.definition: The type of term, either new or renewal.

attributes.name: Term Status
attributes.definition: The status of the Term, either Active or Cancelled.

attributes.name: Pending Cancel Notice Type
attributes.definition: The reason for a pending cancellation, either Inst Nonpay, Renewal Nonpay.

entities.name: Commission Statement
entities.definition: A point in time summary statement of commission earned, paid and held.

attributes.name: Commission Amount
attributes.definition: The amount of commission.

attributes.name: Commission Transaction Type
attributes.definition: Classification of commission on a commission statement as either Earned, Paid, Adjusted or Held.

attributes.name: Commission Type
attributes.definition: Classification of the type of commission, either regular or bonus.

attributes.name: Written Premium
attributes.definition: The written premium transaction that the commission is associated with if applicable.

attributes.name: Term
attributes.definition: The policy term that the commission is associated with if applicable.

attributes.name: Agency
attributes.definition: The agency associated with the commission statement if applicable.

entities.name: Earned Premium
entities.definition: The amount of premium that has been earned out of the premium that has been written.

attributes.name: Earned Premium Date
attributes.definition: The Earned Premium Date

attributes.name: Earned Premium
attributes.definition: The amount of earned premium.

attributes.name: Unearned Premium
attributes.definition: The amount of premium remaining that has not yet been earned.

attributes.name: Written Premium Transaction
attributes.definition: The written premium transaction associated with the earned premium.

entities.name: Insured
entities.definition: The person or entity that is insured by a specific policy coverage.

attributes.name: Insured Name
attributes.definition: The name of the insured.

attributes.name: Insured First Name
attributes.definition: First name of the Insured.

attributes.name: Insured Last Name
attributes.definition: The Last Name of the Insured.

attributes.name: Term
attributes.definition: The term that the party is insured under.

attributes.name: Policy Number
attributes.definition: The system number for the insurance policy.

attributes.name: Policy Symbol
attributes.definition: The symbol for the policy.

attributes.name: Policy State
attributes.definition: The Policy State.

attributes.name: Policy Issue System
attributes.definition: The system that issued the policy.

attributes.name: Account
attributes.definition: The account that the policy is for.

attributes.name: Non Admitted Flag
attributes.definition: The Non Admitted Indicator.

attributes.name: Program
attributes.definition: The policy program.

attributes.name: Underwriting Company
attributes.definition: The Company that underwrote the policy.

entities.name: Risk
entities.definition: The Risk associated with a policy term.

attributes.name: Risk State
attributes.definition: The risk state.

attributes.name: Risk Region
attributes.definition: The region of the risk with groupings defined by states.

attributes.name: Primary Risk Flag
attributes.definition: A flag identifying the primary risk on a term.

attributes.name: Term
attributes.definition: The Term that a Risk is associated with.

entities.name: Underwriting Company
entities.definition: The company that underwrites the policy term.

attributes.name: Company
attributes.definition: The name of the underwriting company.

attributes.name: Company Abbreviation
attributes.definition: The abbreviation for the Underwriting company.

entities.name: Writeoff Line
entities.definition: The lines of invoiced bills that are written off.

attributes.name: Invoice Line
attributes.definition: The invoice line associated with the writeoff line.

attributes.name: Writeoff Date
attributes.definition: The date that a writeoff happens.

attributes.name: Writeoff Amount
attributes.definition: The amount of an invoice line that is written off.

entities.name: Refund Assignment
entities.definition: This defines the relationship of one or more refunds with one or more payments.

attributes.name: Payment Refunded Against
attributes.definition: The payment record that a refund or a portion of a refund was issued against.

attributes.name: Refund
attributes.definition: The refund payment transaction record.

attributes.name: Refund Amount
attributes.definition: The amount of a refund assigned to a specific payment within the record.

attributes.name: Assignment Date
attributes.definition: The date that the refund assignment was made.

attributeClasses.name: Code
attributeClasses.definition: Variable-length alphanumeric representation of longer alphanumeric value.

attributeClasses.name: Location
attributeClasses.definition: Definition of Location

attributeClasses.name: Ordinal
attributeClasses.definition: Ordered sequential value.

attributeClasses.name: Flag
attributeClasses.definition: Indicates the selection of a discrete list of static options.

attributeClasses.name: Description
attributeClasses.definition: Detailed explanation of the object.

attributeClasses.name: Postal Code
attributeClasses.definition: Definition of Postal Code

attributeClasses.name: Rate
attributeClasses.definition: Fractional unitless value. Applies to growth rate, percentage, variance, etc.

attributeClasses.name: Classification
attributeClasses.definition: Definition of Classification

attributeClasses.name: Indicator
attributeClasses.definition: Indicates true or false boolean value.

attributeClasses.name: Quantity
attributeClasses.definition: Number representing the count of items involved in this record. Can be positive or negative.

attributeClasses.name: Count
attributeClasses.definition: Definition of Count

attributeClasses.name: Currency
attributeClasses.definition: Currency amount.

attributeClasses.name: Hash
attributeClasses.definition: Hash text or array of bytes.

attributeClasses.name: Name
attributeClasses.definition: Text or verbal identifier that uniquely identifies with a subgroup. Standard Text type with 200 character maximum size.

attributeClasses.name: Date
attributeClasses.definition: Calendar date with no time component.

attributeClasses.name: Timestamp
attributeClasses.definition: Calendar date with timestamp component.

attributeClasses.name: Time
attributeClasses.definition: Time of day without a calendar date component.

attributeClasses.name: Identifier
attributeClasses.definition: Numeric representation of a value, e.g. "3" for Sales Region 3. Often populated automatically via a database or program sequence. Can be positive or negative.

attributeClasses.name: Amount
attributeClasses.definition: Generic number column, often accompanied by a Unit of Measure column to clarify what the amount is of. Can be positive or negative.

attributeClasses.name: Factor
attributeClasses.definition: A percentage applied by an actuary to a rate. Can be positive or negative.

attributeClasses.name: Integer
attributeClasses.definition: A whole number; can be positive or negative.

attributeClasses.name: Percent
attributeClasses.definition: An allowance, commission, or rate of interest calculated by percent (quantity per one hundred). Can be positive or negative.

attributeClasses.name: Unicode Name
attributeClasses.definition: Text or verbal identifier that uniquely identifies with a subgroup. Variable-length Unicode character string with a maximum length of 200 characters.

attributeClasses.name: Unicode Description
attributeClasses.definition: Detailed explanation of the object. Variable length Unicode character string with a maximum length of 2000.

attributeClasses.name: USPS State Code
attributeClasses.definition: USPS two-character code for a state, protectorate, or military "state".

attributeClasses.name: USPS State Name
attributeClasses.definition: USPS variable-length full name for a state.

attributeClasses.name: Date Time
attributeClasses.definition: A particular month, day, year and time at which some event happened or will happen.

attributeClasses.name: Valid Date Of Birth
attributeClasses.definition: A particular month, day and yer in the past at which an insured could reasonably have been born. e.g. Today - 150 Years. Applied for QA on data entry.

attributeClasses.name: Valid Start Date
attributeClasses.definition: A particular month, day and year now or in the future at which some event could reasonably begin. e.g. Today + 90 Days. Applied for QA on Data Entry.

attributeClasses.name: Source Identifier
attributeClasses.definition: Numeric Identifier from the source system. Typically assigned as a surrogate key by the source system and used as an attribute in the EDW.
